DataElement.preferredName: Or Consortium or Network Professional Organization or Group Telecommunication Address ISO21090.BAG.TEL.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A sequence of digits or characters used to identify a particular telephone, fax, or email of the organization. EXAMPLE(S): The set of digits that serves as the address for a telephone device. Included in the phone number are country, city, and area codes needed to uniquely address the telephone. A URL or e-mail would be similarly described.
